## **8. Challenges and Solutions**

| Challenge | Solution | Outcome |
|-----------|----------|---------|
| Understanding `-a` flag importance in `usermod -a -G` | Without `-a`, `usermod -G` replaces all existing supplementary groups; `-a` appends — confirmed by reading the `usermod` man page | Used `-a -G` consistently to preserve existing memberships |
| `su arosalez` prompting for password | Entered the password set during `passwd arosalez` (`P@ssword1234!`) | Successfully switched to arosalez identity |
| Finding specific event in journalctl output | Used `grep "user NOT in sudoers"` to filter the log stream | Located the denial event immediately without scrolling |
| Distinguishing `/etc/passwd` from `/etc/shadow` | `/etc/passwd` is world-readable and stores account metadata; `/etc/shadow` stores hashed passwords and is restricted to root | Correctly used `/etc/passwd` for username verification |

